# 3D Printed Remote Control Robotic Hand

## Overview
This project implements a wireless, sensor-driven robotic hand using an ESP32 microcontroller. The system enables real-time communication between a sensor-equipped glove and a multi-servo robotic hand, translating input signals into precise mechanical motion.

## Objectives
- Enable wireless communication between input sensors and actuators  
- Implement reliable power distribution for multiple servo motors  
- Develop real-time control logic for accurate motion response  
- Integrate mechanical and electrical components into a functional system  

## System Architecture
The system consists of:
- **ESP32 microcontroller** for wireless communication and control  
- **Sensor inputs** from a glove to capture user motion  
- **Servo motors** to actuate finger movement  
- **3D-printed hand structure** for mechanical implementation  

## Key Features
- Wireless signal transmission using ESP32  
- Real-time sensor-to-actuator mapping  
- Stable power distribution across multiple servos  
- Integrated hardware and mechanical design  
- System debugging and signal optimization for reliable operation  

## Implementation
- Designed embedded control system using ESP32 for communication and signal processing  
- Implemented power distribution to ensure consistent voltage supply to all servo motors  
- Developed control logic to convert sensor inputs into actuator motion  
- Fabricated a custom 3D-printed robotic hand structure  
- Performed system testing and debugging to resolve noise and stability issues  

## Results
- Achieved real-time gesture-based control of robotic fingers  
- Maintained stable operation under multiple actuator loads  
- Improved signal reliability through debugging and optimization  

## Tools & Technologies
- ESP32 (embedded system)  
- Arduino IDE / Embedded C  
- 3D Printing (PLA)  
- Servo motors  
- Electrical circuit design and debugging tools  

## Conclusion
This project demonstrates the integration of embedded systems, power distribution, and mechanical design to create a responsive and reliable robotic control system.
